# 📱 MotherMend: C-Section Recovery Assistant

## 📖 Overview
MotherMend is an AI-powered mobile and web application designed to support Rwandan mothers in monitoring C-section wound healing. Using a convolutional neural network (CNN) for image classification, the app delivers real-time wound status predictions and provides tailored healing guidance or prompts for medical consultation.

## 🔗 GitHub Repository
[Visit the WoundTrack GitHub Repo](https://github.com/esthermbanza/WoundTrack)

## 🛠️ Setup Instructions

### 📋 Prerequisites
- Python 3.10+
- Node.js 18+
- npm or yarn
- Expo CLI
- SQLite
- Git
- Strapi (CMS backend)

### 🧠 AI Model API (FastAPI)
```bash
cd model_api
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn app:app --reload
```

### 📱 Mobile App (React Native - Expo)
```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npx expo start
```

### 🔧 Backend (Strapi CMS)
```bash
cd backend
npm install
npm run develop
```

## 🎨 App Interface Designs
The app features six core screens, designed in Figma and fully implemented:

![WoundTrack Figma Mockups](designs/1bec10e9-mockup.png)

**Screens:**
- Splash / Welcome
- Login
- Home Dashboard
- Upload Wound Photo
- Prediction Result
- Healing Tips

## 🚀 Deployment Plan
- **Model API**: Deploy to Railway or Render using Docker.
- **Strapi CMS**: Deploy to Heroku with SQLite or PostgreSQL.
- **Mobile App**: Build with Expo EAS for Android and iOS.

## 🎥 Video Demonstration
- **Submitted**: July 19, 2025
- **Duration**: 7 minutes
- **Link**: [Watch on YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JpcSdBfA39s)
- **Focus**: Demonstrates app navigation, photo upload, wound prediction, and healing advice.

